    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Clean duplicate and dead videos from a playlist using YouTube and Slack\n\n### How it works\n\n1. A schedule trigger runs the cleanup on a weekly cadence.\n2. The workflow lists every item in the target playlist and looks up each video.\n3. A code step flags duplicates (same video more than once, first kept) and dead entries (deleted, unavailable, or private).\n4. In dry run it only reports; with dry run off it deletes each flagged playlist item in a loop.\n5. Slack receives a summary of what was removed, or a note that the playlist is clean.\n\n### Setup steps\n\n- [ ] Connect a YouTube (Google) OAuth2 credential on the three YouTube nodes.\n- [ ] Set `playlistId` in the Set Playlist and Options node to your playlist ID.\n- [ ] Connect a Slack credential and set `slackChannelId` to your channel.\n- [ ] Keep `dryRun` set to true for the first run, then set it to false to delete for real.\n\n### Customization\n\nChange the schedule interval, or edit the flagging rules in the code node (for example, treat unlisted videos as dead too).",
        "height": 816,
        "width": 592
      },
      "id": "681ba7b4-4055-412a-ad03-dd52074d2b00",
      "name": "Overview",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -688,
        -80
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Safety: dry run is on by default\n\nThis workflow can permanently remove items from your playlist. It ships with `dryRun` set to true, so the first run only reports what it would remove and deletes nothing. Review the Slack summary, then set `dryRun` to false in the Set Playlist and Options node to enable real deletion.",
        "height": 214,
        "width": 584,
        "color": 3
      },
